Independent project management, experiment design and organisation. Writing of scientific papers and project deliverables. Experienced in an international and cross-functional project; in communication by international project meetings and conferences; conflict resolution and problem-solving by international and multi-cultural team collaborations and research experience.

Project details:
Embedded within the MixITiN project, my project combines both a field and a laboratory approach to understand the functioning and metabolic basis of the photosymbioses in radiolarians (rhizaria), which are ecologically important planktonic organisms in the oceans. The major aim will be to characterize trophic exchanges and metabolic strategies of the host and its endosymbiotic microalgae to improve cellular modelling. Applying a combination of stable isotope tracer experiments and photophysiology methods to investigate the interactions between partners in various global warming scenarios (e.g. temperature increase). Additionally, along with physiological characterization, will also study gene expression of symbiotic interactions using transcriptomic analyses on single cell symbiotic organisms.', 'title':
